>     Interesting you should mention that -- I hadn't thought about the
> contrast between American travel habits and other parts of the world.  It
> is probably true that Americans, and I'd say Canadians also, have much more
> freedom to travel long distances within their own language area that
> anywhere else in the world.  You might think the same could apply to
> Australians, but, it's interesting, (I learned this on a trip there), most
> Australians do very little traveling outside their own state.  The
> population there is very concentrated in the six major population areas,
> and few people really get around to the other areas.  On the other hand,
> they do perhaps more frequently take long trips abroad.  Furthermore, when
> I think about Israel and Israelis, you are really very restricted as to how
> far you can easily travel.  Your immediate environs, of course, are not
> very congenial.  I'm just wondering: about how much is the plane fare from
> Israel to London?
>

According to what my sisters say it's $500 in the best case scenario. There 
are cheaper flights to Turkey, though, and many Israelis like to travel 
there.

