Well, according to this:

http://www.hebcal.com/holidays/rosh-hashana.html

Rosh Hashana is on September 16th, (where the feast beforehand is on September 
15th).

>
> <<...baby boy, which they named Matan. They held a celebration of his
> birth....>>
>     Very nice.  Did that include the ceremony which I doubt that I can
> spell, but it sounds like briss or brist?

Brith or more correctly Brith-Milah. Well, the brith took place on the baby's 
8th day by a Mohel, with a usual traditional ceremony. The celebration took 
place some time afterwards, when the baby had already been circumcized.

